; utility function for packing the equals elements
((fn packer [result previous collection-param]
  ;work on collection
  ;but only if collection has some elements
  (if-let [[head & args] (seq collection-param)]
    (if (= head (first previous))
      ; if head, i.e. the first element in the collection is
      ; equals to the first element of the sub-list in check
      ; then add the head in this sub-list (previous) and call packer forward
      ; with the rest of the collection, called args
      (packer result (conj previous head) args)
      ; else add the previous list in the result, 
      ; create a new previous list to work on and go forward with packer
      (packer (conj result previous) [head] args)
    )    
 ; )
  ;if the collection is empty then return the last conjunction
  (conj result previous))
)

; the packer function start with this initial arguments:
; result: [] an empty collection
; previous: [(first collection-param)] the first element of the collection
; collection: (rest collection-param) the rest of the collection
[] [(first collection-param)] (rest collection-param)
))

  (let [coll (seq coll)
        f (fn [x] (= x (first coll)))]
    (when (not (nil? coll))
      (cons (take-while f coll)
            (pack-seq (drop-while f coll))))))

(fn pack
  [some-seq]
  (reverse 
   (reduce 
    (fn [acc e]
      (if (= (first (first acc)) e)

        (cons 
         (list e) 
         acc)))
    [] some-seq)))

(fn compress
  [s]
  (let [reduce-fn (fn [coll v] 
                    (let [collvec (vec coll)
                          prefix (if (empty? collvec) [] (pop collvec))

      :else (cons current (pack s)))))

(fn pack [l]
  (letfn [(gather-duplicates-aux
           [l a]
           (if (empty? l)
             '()
             (if (= (first l) a)
               (cons (first l) (gather-duplicates-aux (rest l) a))
               '())))
          (gather-duplicates [l]
                             (gather-duplicates-aux l (first l)))
          (remove-duplicates-aux
           [l a]
           (if (empty? l)
             '()
             (if (= (first l) a)
               (remove-duplicates-aux (rest l) a)
               l)))
          (remove-duplicates [a]
                             (remove-duplicates-aux a (first a)))]
    (if (empty? l)
      '()
      (cons
       (gather-duplicates l)
       #_(let [dup (gather-duplicates l)]
         (if (= (count dup) 1)
           (first dup)
           dup))
       (pack (remove-duplicates l))))))

(fn afkt [coll]
  (let [pack-1 (fn pack [res prev coll]
    (if (empty? coll)
      res
      (if (empty? res)
        (pack
          (list (list (first coll)))
          (first coll)
          (drop 1 coll)
         )
        (pack
         (if (= (first coll) prev)
            (concat (drop-last res)  ( list (conj (last res) prev)))
           (concat res (list (list (first coll)))))
         (first coll)
         (drop 1 coll)))))]
    (pack-1 '() nil coll)))
